          "date": "2013-08-15 20:35:46.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-107 build: Add abitilty to remove failover startup scripts",
        "message": "LU-107 build: Add abitilty to remove failover startup scripts\n\nThis patch will allow users/vendors who do not want to remove the\nhigh availability support(failover) from the source but want to\nremove its startup scripts from the RPM build package.\nThe command line option \"--disable-HA\" given to the configure script\nwill remove the startup scritps. Default option is to enable the high\navailabity support by installing these startup scripts but will\nprevent the old or modified one to be overwritten.\n\nlustre.spec.in - remove the startup scripts from the RPM build\n                 or add them without overwriting the old modified one\n\nlustre/autoconf/lustre-core.m4 - add new option --disable-HA.\n\nlustre/scripts/Makefile.am - remove/add the startup scripts from/to\n                              variable init_SCRIPTS.\n\nSigned-off-by: Young Jong Pao <n16490@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I3ac5c13b9b7107fdc960d865e540be7e1d59dc2b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
